description.en-US:
Come hear how God is working powerfully in and through young adults in their 20s and 30s at The Porch. We’ll share our ministry vision, strategy, and methods; discuss principles for reaching and challenging young adults to live out their purpose in Christ; and present practical approaches in addressing ministry challenges. Let us help you reach this generation for Christ.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

Watermark's Operations Team will share best practices for leading the operations of your church. Learn the unique organizational challenges facing senior church leaders, including finances and budgeting, hiring, staff care, leadership best practices, strategic planning and execution, decision-making, and more.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

Learn about Watermark's unique marriage ministries and practical steps to lead couples in your church more effectively. Whether you want to improve your existing marriage ministry, overhaul your strategy, or start from the ground up, this workshop will help you make disciples in the context of marriage and the local church.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

How do we challenge individuals to take the next step in their walk with Christ and find a clear path toward discipleship? Come learn how Watermark seeks to equip our Members to be and make disciples in any life stage. Watermark’s Equipping Team will discuss transformative Bible studies, devotional and apologetic strategies, faithful stewardship, and other opportunities to equip your church with a deeper understanding of God’s Word.

*Workshops require advance registration during conference signups.*

re|engage is a safe place for married couples to grow in their marriage. Each week, participants hear from couples whose marriages have been transformed, learn practical ways to grow in oneness with their spouse, and gain insight from others in a small group setting as they walk through 16 lessons. You will have the opportunity to join large group time and the "Newcomers" session.
Shoreline is Watermark's monthly gathering of high school students for worship, teaching, and connection. We are committed to guiding future generations to follow Jesus and be the Church.
Observe from rehearsal to execution as Shane & Shane talk through the worship set for Session 5 of the conference.

We are making our staff members from every ministry area availabe to you. Our senior leaders, worship directors, children's ministry admins, finance coordinators, student directors, and even IT team will be available to talk. We don't claim to have all the answers, but if you want to hear a different perspective, bounce some ideas off someone else, or hear what's worked (and what hasn't worked) in our experience, sign up for a time slot.

Don't wait long to reserve your time. Slots will fill up quickly.

The Porch challenges young adults to take the next step of faith and connect with others who will spur them on to full devotion to Christ. This ministry challenges young adults to put their faith into practice and serves as an introduction to participation in the local church. 

Attendees will have the opporunity to join for the weekly Porch leader meeting at 6:00 pm before the start of The Porch at 7:00pm.

In Christ, people can be set free from the destruction of sin. Learn about the radical healing people are receiving in Christ through re:generation, our Biblical 12-step recovery ministry. Through the gospel, daily abiding, authentic community, confession, repentance, and forgiveness, entire churches can change and grow.

Attendees will have the opportunity to experience all aspects of re:generation including the weekly leaders meeting, large group meeting to hear teaching and testimonies, and a mock small group lead by an experienced leader.

Merge is an premarital discipleship ministry designed for engaged and seriously dating couples. It's a chance to seek wisdom and receive counsel about marriage from  in a safe, fun, and authentic environment. Merge addresses common questions and challenges from a biblical perspective. Class dynamics include: large group teaching, small group discussion with mentors, and weekly homework.

I grew up in Garland, Texas and made my way to Texas A&M upon graduation. I spent 6 years there and loved every minute of it. I graduated with a degree in early childhood and have used that in multiple different setting. All throughout my life I can see God’s loving hand guiding me along the best pathway for my life. (Psalm 32:8) Whether it was changing where I could go to high school last minute or planting TBarM Sports Camp staff in my path, He has provided countless people and experiences for me to taste and see that He is good. (Psalm 34:8) After 6 different jobs in the 5 years following graduation I finally landed here at Watermark. Never in my dreams did I think I would get to be a part of a mission like this. It is a joy to journey with people I love calling all families to run after Jesus wholeheartedly!

A few of my favorite things…

I love the Lord and I am thankful that He deals with me in a gracious and personal way, especially when I am diligent to give Him time and space.

I love kids and their simple and fun way of facing life and believe one of the best ways to impact their lives is to impact their parents’ lives.

I love my people (aka peeps) and therefore spend most of my free time with friends doing fun things… mostly eating!

I love food, especially queso from Torchy’s, ice cream from Marble Slab, chicken strips from Bubba’s, and salad from Salata.

I love to travel and see new places. Once a year I take an alone trip. Sometimes to really cool places.

I love taking pictures of all different kinds of subjects, but especially God’s creation… whether landscape or person!

And lastly I love questions and the way they draw out deep conversation.

Just some test of an announcement. You should delete this when we have more announcements! Test [link](https://www.watermark.org/).

description.en-US: Learn helpful principles for engaging and shepherding women facing difficult situations such as unfaithfulness, addiction, and abuse.

Merge prepares seriously dating and engaged couples for marriage by addressing common challenges from a biblical perspective in a fun and authentic environment. Join us for our weekly large group teaching time, and small group discussion with couples.
